Version:          1.0.1
Release:          2%{?dist}
Summary:          Methods for Estimating Causal Effects from Observational Data

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-igraph 
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-rcdd 
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-rje 
Requires:         R-CRAN-igraph 
Requires:         R-CRAN-rcdd 
Requires:         R-CRAN-rje 

%description
Estimate causal effects of one variable on another, currently for binary
data only. Methods include instrumental variable bounds, adjustment by a
given covariate set, adjustment by an induced covariate set using a
variation of the PC algorithm, and an effect bounding method (the Witness
Protection Program) based on covariate adjustment with observable
independence constraints.

